  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-02-13",
    "date": "2009-02-28T16:50:45Z",
    "text": "Assisting Doctors to Obtain Proficient and Transmissible Health Information Technology Act of 2009 or the ADOPT HIT Act of 2009 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow medical care providers to expense (i.e., deduct all costs in the current taxable year) up to $250,000 of the cost of health care information technology used primarily for the electronic creation, maintenance, and exchange of medical care information.\n\nDirects the Secretary of Health and Human Services to develop standards for hardware, software, and support services for the electronic exchange of health information."
  },
